        <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersAnimals10"/>
        <p><a href="ch73s03.html#MonstersAnimals9">Badgers</a> attack with their sharp claws and teeth.</p>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id2270368"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersAnimals11"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Rage (Ex):</strong></span> A <a href="ch73s03.html#MonstersAnimals9">badger</a> that takes damage in combat flies into a berserk rage on its next turn, clawing and biting madly until either it or its opponent is dead. It gains +4 to Strength, +4 to Constitution, and -2 to Armor Class. The creature cannot end its rage voluntarily.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id2270406"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersAnimals12"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Skills:</strong></span> A <a href="ch73s03.html#MonstersAnimals9">badger</a> has a +4 racial bonus on <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills137">Escape Artist</a> checks.</p>
